
[1.3.4] — 2026-03-10
Download modes: added robust 3-mode settings with proper mutual exclusivity.
Settings stability: fixed the checkbox-state.
Folder workflow: improved one-folder flow for single and bulk downloads, with persistent folder path and quick change action.
Bulk downloads: optimized large archive handling with duplicate-skip logic, clearer progress states and notifications.
Autoplay performance: reworked thumbnail autoplay pipeline to reduce UI freezes/lag while keeping full-page preview behavior.
Thumbnail optimization: lowered preview quality for faster loading in both Videos and Images tabs.
Settings added: you can choose how many videos to download and many other settings
UI: Extensive cleaning and refinement of many graphic elements


[1.3.3] — 2026-03-09
Grid: Added Grid view with nested generations + compilation download.
Images: Updated delete flow to Grok’s new delete‑post endpoint.
Downloads: Save‑as prompt for all downloads + “File ready” banner + sound.
UI: Whole UI heavily refined and tooltips added across actions.

[1.3.2] — 2026-03-08
Pagination: Added First/Last + page jump for faster navigation.
Performance: Thumbnails hover fix and lighter UI rendering.
Downloads: Page downloads with clearer UI and tooltips. 
Share: You can now share your link.
Memory: Minimized per-item payloads and tighter caching.
UI: You can see now the current Grok-Viewer version clicking on the Github icon 

[1.3.1] - 2026-03-08

Added pagination (32 items per page) for Videos and Images with Prev/Next and Last controls.

Changed
Page cache is capped to current ±1 to reduce memory.
Downloads are now page‑scoped (“Download Page”).
Reduced in‑memory item payloads to keep the UI responsive on huge libraries.


[1.3.0] - 2026-03-07

Archive downloads now display a “File ready” button and play a notification sound when the file is prepared.
Large library downloads now show a progress bar under the download area.

Changed
Download All is now sequential (instead of parallel), making it significantly more reliable on large libraries.
UI layout refined: improved action button placement, footer text, progress panel organization, and a more neutral background for readability.

[1.2.9] - 2026-03-02
Added

New Images tab with a full lightbox experience: open, navigate, download all, and delete.
Optional thumbnail autoplay (disabled by default).
Video sorting by creation time.
Ability to hide the “Content Moderated” moderation toast.
Purge Cache button to recover when the extension becomes unresponsive or stuck.

Changed

First launch now loads Favorites immediately, then performs a single initial refresh afterward.
Download All improved for large libraries by splitting downloads into parts when needed.
Background and overlay layers simplified to improve UI responsiveness and overall performance.
Refresh behavior is now manual only (no background auto-refresh).

Fixed
Delete Images now removes all images in a single pass and automatically purges cache after completion.
